CREATED:20260421T201143Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260421T201143Z
UID:10013736-1777802400-1777816800@visityolo.com
SUMMARY:Loopalooza Bike Ride
DESCRIPTION:In celebration of May is Bike Month\, the City of Davis invites the community to hop on their bikes for the 16th Annual Loopalooza on Sunday\, May 3\, from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. In partnership with Bike Davis and local organizations\, this beloved\, family-friendly tradition features a community bike ride with activity stations along the 12-mile loop through Davis. \n  \nParticipants can start anywhere along the loop\, ride in either direction and enjoy a variety of interactive activities\, community booths and food options along the way. Riders are encouraged to visit multiple stations\, explore Davis’ greenbelts and parks and connect with neighbors and friends. \n  \nAll participants are required to complete a liability waiver prior to riding. Waivers can be completed in advance or on the day of the event. To complete the waiver\, access the event map and learn more\, visit: www.cityofdavis.org/Loopalooza. \n  \nThis year’s 11 activity stations will feature the following community organizations and activities: \n  \n\nPatwin Elementary School:\n\nS. Bicycling Hall of Fame penny-farthing bicycle photo\nOddfellows Spin Art Bikes\nZim Cuisine\nAfter CCE Bike Swap Clearance Sale. If you missed the 13th Annual Citywide Bike Swap on April 12 and are looking for a bike\, come to the After Swap Clearance Sale. You’ll find rock-bottom deals on gently used bike and bike related items for both kids and adults. All bikes need a new home\, so are priced to sell! Questions?  Email: davisbikeswap@gmail.com or visit website: www.davisbikeswap.org\n\n\n\n  \n\nSycamore Park:\n\nCity of Davis Teen Leadership Council lawn games\nGirl Scouts helmet check\n\n\n\n  \n\nCommunity Park:\n\nYolo-Solano Air Quality Management District information\nYolo County Sustainability Team bike safety information\nYolo County Library bicycle library\nCity of Davis Skate Park information\nDavis Bike Park Alliance\nKona Ice\n\n\n\n  \n\nHolmes Junior High:\n\nUC Davis Design Students Bike Scavenger Hunt Teaser\nSpin Micromobility test rides\n\n\n\n  \n\nMace Ranch Park:\n\nCool Davis lawn games\nCity of Davis Sustainability Team games and environmental information on climate-ready landscapes\nAYSO Soccer goal shooting\n\n\n\n  \n\nMontgomery Elementary School:\n\nScouts and Davis Police Department Bike Rodeo\n\n\n\n  \n\nDavis Commons/UC Davis Arboretum:\n\nYolo Commute May is Bike Month and Yolo Commute information\nSacramento Area Bicycle Advocates (SABA) Bike Month information\nCity of Davis I-80/Richards Boulevard Project Outreach\nBohart Museum of Entomology showcase\nYolo County Health and Human Services Agency helmet checks and bike raffle\n\n\n\n  \n\nUC Davis Hoagland Hall:\n\nUC Davis Bike Program safety information\nASUCD Bike Barn\n\n\n\n  \n\nUC Davis ARC Lawn:\n\nWhole Earth Festival Preview\nUC Davis Fellows Bubble Station\nUC Davis Marching Band performing (time TBA)\n\n\n\n  \n\nBlue Ridge Road:\n\nASUCD Housing and Transportation Advisory Committee bike safety spin wheel\nCycling Without Age photobooth\n\n\n\n  \n\nEvenstar Lane:\n\nWhymcycles test rides\nBike Davis bike safety and encouragement information and photobooth
URL:https://visityolo.com/event/loopalooza-bike-ride/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visityolo.com/wp-content/uploads/tower-electric-bikes-9gYZC7ti9rE-unsplash.jpg
END:VEVENT
