SUMMARY:Whole Earth Festival
DESCRIPTION:The Whole Earth Festival (WEF) at UC Davis is a major free\, three-day student-run festival held annually on Mother’s Day Weekend\, attracting over 30\,000 visitors to the UC Davis Quad. It promotes wellness\, environmental sustainability\, and activism through music\, art\, workshops\, and food. The event is known for being a zero-waste\, eco-friendly gathering. 
